<plot>An irreverent look at the media stereotypes of Asian women and how three Asian American artists are making a difference through their work. A young cartoonist, Lela Lee (creator of the Angry Little Asian Girl); a writer/actress/comedian, Amy Hill (All-American Girl); and a TV/film actress, Ming-Na (Joy Luck Club, Mulan, ER) share their experiences growing up Asian American and how these experiences influence their work today.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?401015</url></doc>
